.LE
10-April-1992 - All modules
.list
.LE;^*TRIANG, TRIEDIT, TRIDER, TRIGRID\*#-#These programs now run under
DECwindows Motif by using the shareable image pointed to by LSL$DTM__GKSSHR.
This is defined by LSL$COM:DTMCREATEINI to point to a Motif, UIS or NULL image
depending on the device being used.
.LE;^*DTMCREATEINI\*#-#The logical LSL$DTM__GKSSHR will be defined to point to
a new image appropriate to the device being used. The new DTMCREATE images are
LSL$EXE:DTM__GKSMOTIFSHR.EXE for Motif, LSL$EXE:DTM__GKSUISSHR.EXE for UIS
and LSL$EXE:DTM__GKSNULLSHR.EXE for a non-graphical device.
.END LIST
.!...........................................................................
.!
.LE
12-October-1992 - All modules
.list
.LE;^*TRIANG, TRIEDIT, TRIDER, TRIGRID\*#-#These programs now obtain their
internal resolution as defined by the logical name LSL$DTMCREATE__RESOLUTION.
All input coordinates are scaled into integer form in TRIANG to speed up
calculation and the range for these was previously 0 to 300000. However, this
was not sufficient for some datasets and caused TRIANG to become 'stuck' or
produce the STOPNOD error message as it was unable to distinguish between
points which were very close together.

.P 0;Increasing this resolution may prevent this happening on some datasets and
could be done if problems do occur in the triangulation.

.P 0;The logical must be defined to lie between 300000 and 10000000 in order
that manipulations on the scaled input coordinates will safely fit into a
32-bit integer. If the logical is undefined, the resolution will default to
300000 to maintain compatability with existing datasets.

.NOTE IMPORTANT
It is essential that the logical value LSL$DTMCREATE__RESOLUTION remains the
same when going from TRIANG all the way through to TRIGRID on a particular
dataset. If the resolution is altered between any of the stages, unpredictable
results will occur and programs may fail.
.END NOTE

.LE;^*Reference Manual\*#-#The documentation of each module has been modified
to include a description of the new logcal.

.END LIST
